@comgra Hi, you need to add `tweet_mode=extended` to the API and whenever replace `.text` with `.full_text`. This should get the full version of the tweets unless they are retweets. Retweets have `RT @<username>: ` at the beginning and these sometimes get truncated. To solve this check if `.retweeted_status` exists, if it does then you need to use `.retweeted_status.full_text`. Below is an example of my working code:

```python
api = twitter.Api(consumer_token, consumer_secret, access_token, access_token_secret, tweet_mode="extended")

tweets = api.GetSearch(term="#gameofthrones", lang="en", count=100)

for tweet in tweets:
    if tweet.retweeted_status is None:
        print(tweet.full_text)
    else:
        print(tweet.retweeted_status.full_text)
```

Hope this helps!

