The calculation requires the q-score bins, which are in the header (shared among all q-metrics). The header is apart of the metric set.

So to calculate the total >= Q30 for an arbitrary tile/cycle, you can do the following:

 q_metrics q_metric_set;
 read_interop(argv[1], q_metric_set);
 q_metric& metric0 = q_metric_set.at(0);
std::cout << "Total >= Q30: " << metric0.total_over_qscore(30, q_metric_set.bins()) << std::endl;

```javascript
#!/usr/bin/env node
const spawnteract = require('spawnteract')

spawnteract.launch('python2').then(kernel => {
        // Returns
        // kernel.spawn <-- The running process, from child_process.spawn(...)
