@tisc0 I'm very interested in more detail over exactly how you installed and ran this to end up with that problem.

When I built the centos7 certbot packages I tested them in AWS with no problems - certainly not what you have described or this issue describes.

It's a terrible idea to install a fedora rpm like that directly on centos7 - especially with a core package like pyOpenSSL.

@jekbradbury in the end, it seems that the problem was caused by the conversion from `array.array` to `torch.tensor`. The memory footprint of loading the entire large dimensional vectors turns out to be manageable.

The filtering approach is problematic to implement due to caching of the vectors once loaded, which happens at the same time as filtering. This would mean that some name for the cached file should be generated based on the words in the vocabulary in order to differ between vocabs, which feels like unnecessary as the memory issues have been resolved.

